dct_title_s: Polygon Features of the Armstrong Redwoods State Reserve Habitat Assessment, California, 1997-1998
dct_description_sm: This polygon layer represents a merged shapefile of all polygonal features created for the Armstrong Redwoods State Reserve Habitat Assessment for 1997-1998. Polygonal features within this file include boundary indications, bridges, culverts and trees.

This shapefile was created for the purposes of providing one GIS layer that describes the polygon features assessed during the Armstrong Redwoods State Reserve Habitat Assessment. These features are intended for the purposes of mapping and assessment.
This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
